{"type": "article", "id": 27918, "title": "原子挂钟", "description": "", "date": "2016-06-08T07:24:53Z", "super_tag": "", "tags": [], "category": 25, "column": 28, "author": 400262, "comment_count": 2, "praise_count": 23, "image": "img/article/article_show/20160702123432dBEw0J6N2M8ysY9b.jpg", "contents": "\n\n<p>          </p>\n<p>即使是再微小的物理量也能产生有趣的创意。来自德国的 Michael Schielke 就根据原子的形状和周围的电子运动为灵感，设计了这款极简的铝制挂钟 <a href=\"https://www.behance.net/gallery/37900345/ATOM-CLOCK-CONCEPT\">ATOM</a>。这款挂钟并没有钟面，通过指针末端圆形凹槽所在的位置辨别时间。更特别的是你还可以通过手势控制它回到休眠状态，只有鼓掌两次之后时针才会指示当前的时间，起到了节能的作用。ATOM 目前还是概念产品，尚未投入实际生产。</p>\n<div class=\"com-insert-images medium-insert-active medium-insert-images-wide\">\n<figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201607021234294aNr3nEYBuD1I0jW.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"medium-insert-image-active\" data-ratio=\"1.0\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n<figcaption class=\"medium-insert-caption-placeholder\"></figcaption></figure><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702123430eawG7Rt21IoAnPDc.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.0\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201607021234309rpcbvFaugWky3sL.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.0\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702123431oQFIsqzLv3AgJbhX.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.0\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure>\n</div>\n\n"}